BUDGET
  Simulate your nation's entire next update and report the money.

SYNTAX
  budget
  budg

DESCRIPTION
  Runs the same production/maintenance/build logic the real update
  would run next, on throwaway in-memory copies of your sectors,
  ships, planes, and land units — nothing is written to the
  database. Prints an itemized cost/income rollup for your nation,
  plus a breakdown of which of your producing sectors are
  capacity-limited right now and why.

  This is the nation-wide counterpart to 'production' (which only
  simulates output sector-by-sector): 'production' tells you what
  one sector will make, 'budget' tells you whether your whole
  economy is trending up or down, and whether you can afford to
  start something big (a carrier group, a new factory chain) before
  the next update lands.

  THIS IS A PREVIEW, NOT A GUARANTEE. Bot activity, other players'
  actions, or anything else that changes state between now and the
  real update can change the actual outcome.

OUTPUT — COST/INCOME ROLLUP
  Sector Type            Per-sector-type production this update,
                          with unit count and dollar cost.
  Ship/Plane/Unit/Sector  Building and maintenance costs, broken out
    building/maintenance  by category (a ship under construction costs
                          differently than one just sitting there).
  Military payroll        Mil pay plus reserve pay.
  Total expenses          Sum of everything above.
  Income from taxes       Civilian + uncompensated-worker tax income.
  Income from bars        Bank interest income from bars on hand.
  Total income            Sum of both income lines.
  Balance forward          Your current treasury (right now).
  Estimated delta          Total income minus total expenses.
  Estimated new treasury   Balance forward + estimated delta.

  If the estimated new treasury is negative, you'll see a warning:
  once a nation's treasury goes negative, sectors stop producing,
  stop distributing, and stop delivering (see 'info nation' for how
  a negative treasury freezes an economy) — so this is your early
  warning to hold off on new spending, not just a curiosity.

OUTPUT — CAPACITY SHORTFALLS
  For each of your sectors that's eligible to produce (>=60% eff,
  has a production commodity) but isn't actually producing at
  capacity right now, this section tallies why, grouped by cause:
    missing <commodity>            — out of an input material (lcm,
                                      hcm, oil, etc.) — the same
                                      thing 'production's use1-3 vs
                                      max1-3 columns show per-sector,
                                      just rolled up nation-wide.
    low natural resource (...)     — the sector's mineral/fertility/
                                      oil/uranium deposit is too low.
    insufficient workforce (avail) — not enough available work units.
    nation level too low           — tech or education level is below
    (tech/education)                 what tech centers/research labs
                                      need to produce at all.

  If every producing sector is running at capacity, you'll just see
  a one-line confirmation instead of a list.

EXAMPLE
  budget            check your nation's projected next-update finances

SEE ALSO
  production  nation  power  show product  info happiness
